pull.title: doc: Update OpenBSD build guide for 6.4
pull.body:
Includes a commit from #14314.
The `disable-dependency-tracking ` workaround is still required to run `./configure` (cc #14404).
`gmake check -j4` pass.
`src/bitcoind` runs and "starts" syncing.

issue.title: Trivial: gitignore contents of db4 folder
issue.body: A lot of stuff is generated by running `./contrib/install_db4.sh .`. I had to ignore it to avoid committing to my repo and I'm sure many others must do the same.

events.body:
If anyone testing this gets stuck running `./configure` and/or doesn't want to pass `disable-dependency-tracking`, a workaround is to downgrade automake to `1.15.1`. See my comment [here](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/14404#issuecomment-431542526) for more info.

If you have trouble running the functional tests, seeing errors like:
```
UnicodeEncodeError: ascii codec can't encode character ...
```
you might need to `export LC_CTYPE=en_US.UTF-8`.
I cannot test this as my VM environment refuses to run OpenBSD 6.4. I think this is straightforward enough, though.
